2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.0860fdc9-1de2-4dc3-9912-1b037b6d66d0.description=This workflow adds/ updates the component properties to Instance using Artifact APIs. onlyUpdate\: yes/no yes - To update values of existing properties no - To add and/or update properties keyValuePairs\: If you want to Add/update new properties\: property1 PUBLIC INTEGER 5 property2 PUBLIC STRING abc xyz If you want to only update the values of existing properties\: property1 5 property2 abc xyz 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.2393e79b-63ef-4b80-ac34-3c6d1d207cb6.description=
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.

2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.68deff8e-8a2c-4740-b1aa-873bb396cd9a.description=Flex up a VM to the specific CPU Memory and Disk that is requested. Input Parameters\: serviceName -name of the service that will be created with this flow VCenterHost - vCenter host to execute against VCenterUsername - vCenter username VCenterPassword - vCenter password. virtualMachine - This is the virtual machine that will be flexed. dataStore - target datastore on the vCenter host for the VMs hostSystem - target ESX host for the VMs cpuCount - number of cpus the virtual machine should have. memSize - amount of memory the virtual machine should have. addDisk - whether or not disk should be added to the vm. Responses\: success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0 failure - otherwise Result Fields\: NA 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.86177592-3dfd-497c-8d7a-17ac96f70680.prompt=User Identifier 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.8bd190a9-b486-4b11-94ff-27431dddafe9.prompt=User Identifier 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.95f03535-6f6e-47dc-b2f3-8a4e52ae08ce.description=Check if there is atleast 2 server components in Deployed State to perform Flexin Input Parameters\: serverIds - List of server UUIDs separated by a delimiter delimiter - the list delimiter. userIdentifier - OO Application UUID to authorize a REST Call Responses\: success - if there are > 1 valid server failure - if there are <\= 1 valid server Result Fields\: NA 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.ab063cbd-3d34-4b74-9b04-4cc72f9e9000.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal
2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.c3d1e58e-867c-4cb4-addb-410a84be1513.description=This workflow adds/ updates the component properties to Instance using Artifact APIs. onlyUpdate\: yes/no yes - To update values of existing properties no - To add and/or update properties keyValuePairs\: If you want to Add/update new properties\: property1 PUBLIC INTEGER 5 property2 PUBLIC STRING abc xyz If you want to only update the values of existing properties\: property1 5 property2 abc xyz 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.c7e801a9-8bc1-4fd1-867d-09a90d8bf864.description=
This workflow retrieves all the child components of the parent component id sorted by created time.

Inputs\:

artifactId		- Component id for which the child components will be retrieved
userIdentifier	- User Identifier to pass to the wrapper flow to retrieve the child components

Returns\:
childIds	- List of child component ids each separated by ","

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.d597f59c-1db5-40bd-88b5-2ee7751c3fb9.prompt=User Identifier 2ba3028f-504e-4624-ada0-cdf74d418646.description=
This flow runs a flex up/flex down action on a server group. It identifies all the servers in a group and runs the flex memory action on each server to set the memory configuration based on the user input.

Inputs\:
userIdentifier	\: The user identifier associated with the CSA login	
artifactId		\: The server group component ID
host		\: The hostname or IP address of the vCenter provider
user		\: The name of the user account to login to the vCenter provider
password		\: The password of the user account to login to the vCenter provider
port		\: The port used by the vCenter provider
protocol		\: The protocol used by the vCenter provider
cpuCount		\: The number of cpus to be flexed
memoryInMb		\: The memory in MB that the server should be flex to


Response\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - there are no more results to retrieve.
